# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Tutorial 9: render the two deformation modes used to extract the elastic
# constants of diamond-cubic silicon, each as its OWN deformed cell:
#   * diamond-c11.png -- an (exaggerated) uniaxial tensile strain along z,
#                        whose stress response gives C11 (and C12)
#   * diamond-c44.png -- an (exaggerated) yz shear strain, whose stress
#                        response gives C44
# The strains are enlarged well beyond the +/-1% used in elastic.lmp so the
# distortion is visible.  Illustrates change_box (remap), and the LAMMPS-GUI
# rendering features autobond / graphics/objects / graphics/labels.
# Open in LAMMPS-GUI and run, or:  lmp -in visualize.lmp

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Panel 1: uniaxial tensile strain along z  ->  C11
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
units metal
boundary p p p
atom_style atomic
# quarter-cell origin shift (as in Tutorial 1) so no atoms sit on box faces
lattice diamond 5.431 origin 0.125 0.125 0.125
region box block 0 2 0 2 0 2
create_box 1 box
create_atoms 1 box
mass 1 28.0855
pair_style sw
pair_coeff * * ../Si.sw Si

# exaggerated 15% tensile strain along z (atoms remapped affinely)
change_box all z scale 1.15 remap

# red tensile arrows along +/- z, centered on the cell
fix fnorm all graphics/objects 1 &
    arrow 1  5.43 5.43 13.5  5.43 5.43 19.0  0.6 0.3
run 0
write_dump all image diamond-c11.png type type adiam 1.45 &
    autobond 3.0 0.45 &
    view 80 -14 center s 0.5 0.5 0.7 zoom 1.1 size 1000 1200 &
    shiny 0.2 ssao yes 4539 0.3 fsaa yes &
    fix fnorm const 0 0 &
    modify backcolor white boxcolor midnightblue &
    color goldsi 0.83 0.66 0.22 acolor 1 goldsi &
    fcolor fnorm firebrick

clear

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Panel 2: yz shear strain  ->  C44
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
units metal
boundary p p p
atom_style atomic
lattice diamond 5.431 origin 0.125 0.125 0.125
region box block 0 2 0 2 0 2
create_box 1 box
create_atoms 1 box
mass 1 28.0855
pair_style sw
pair_coeff * * ../Si.sw Si

# exaggerated yz shear: tilt the box by ~15% of its height (atoms remapped).
# NOTE: change_box tilt defaults to LATTICE units -- use "units box" for Ang.
change_box all triclinic
change_box all yz final 1.3 remap units box

# green shear couple in front of the crystal (top -> +y, bottom -> -y)
fix fshear all graphics/objects 1 &
    arrow 1  5.43 4.0 15.0   5.43 11.0 15.0   0.6 0.3 
run 0
write_dump all image diamond-c44.png type type adiam 1.45 &
    autobond 3.0 0.45 &
    view 80 -14 center s 0.5 0.5 0.7 zoom 1.1 size 1000 1200 &
    shiny 0.2 ssao yes 4539 0.3 fsaa yes &
    fix fshear const 0 0 &
    modify backcolor white boxcolor midnightblue &
    color goldsi 0.83 0.66 0.22 acolor 1 goldsi &
    fcolor fshear forestgreen
